Scene 1 - 0 : Here's Looking at you Kid

<LIGHTS: House lights down. Follow spot up on stage to show Reggie talking into his microphone. Stage
is set up with two safes set into the flats.>

<As Reggie is talking, one spy all in white comes through the audiences from the direction of the sound booth.>

Reggie: <In a soft voice> Yes ladies and gentlemen we're here for the first live coverage of the annual worldwide
spy olympics. <Noticing Whitey> And I believe this is one of the contestants of today's first event, your favorite,
the secret dossier stealing competition.

<LIGHTS: As the rest of the lights come up, the spy in white pull a paper bag over his head. The interview continues
with the spy hidden in this manner.>

Reggie: Darling disguise, sir. Reminds me of a certain entertainment reviewer for the Imprint. Now tell me, are there 
normally so few people at these contests? You seem to be the only contestant here today.

Whitey: There aren't many spies who are interested in taking part in such a public event. I mean, spies prefer to work
behind the scenes.

<A thousand spy heads suddenly appear around the stage: from behind the piano, the trap door, the big doors at the 
back, etc. They appear for two seconds, then disappear.>

Reggie: So if every other spy avoided the contest because of publicity, why are you here?

Whitey: There won't really be any publicity; this contest is being broadcast by CKMS. ## The University of Waterloo student radio station ##

<Blacky enters, runs straight towards one of the safes, and begins to twirl the dial.>

Reggie: Just a minute, ma'am, the contest hasn't quite started yet.

Blacky: Oh. Sorry.

Reggie: Would you mind joining us, ma'am?

Blacky: Why, are you coming apart?

Reggie: Very witty, ma'am. Well ladies and gentlemen, we've been talking with... <points microphone at Whitey>

Whitey: John Smith.

Reggie: ...and...<points microphone at Blacky>

Blacky: John Smith.

Reggie: I see. Well, we're about to start the contest, so good luck to you both and may the best spy win. All set? Then GO!

<Reggie shoots starting pistol in air. There is a loud squawk and the famous rubber chicken falls from the canopy. The spies
run to either side of the stage and pull out their tools. Blacky has a stethoscope and earmuffs. Whitey has a hand drill with
a long extension cord on it. He plugs the extension cord into the outlet between the safes. While they prepare, Reggie goes on.>

Reggie: The object of this contest is very simple, as are the contestants. The first spy to open the safe and steal its top-secret
contents is the winner and folks, anything goes! And our contestants have selected their tools now. John Smith has chosen a drill.
It looks like he's using the good old brute force and ignorance method. Beside him, John Smith is using a stethoscope. It's obvious
that she likes to do things with style and finesse. I'm sure we'll see a real fight for the title tonight!

<The two spies start to work on their respective safes. Whitey sets up his drill and starts to use it to drill around the safe.
He makes a loud drill sound, BRRUMM, BRUMM. In a few moments, he sets down the drill, puts some dynamite against the door and runs to the front of the stage with a plunger. He hits the plunger and there is a loud explosion that knocks open both doors. The spies run inside.>

Reggie: Ladies and gentlement, both spies have their safes open. All that remains is for them to steal the contents and reveal them here on stage. I wonder what they'll find.

<Blacky comes out of her safe.>

Reggie: Well, what was in there? Gold? Jewelry? Government Secrets?

Blacky: ## Surely, this should be Whitey? ## <Leaping out of his door> It's...astounding.

Whitey: ## And this should be Blacky ## Yes, it's FASS '81!

<The doors swing open and the entire cast streams in for the Opening Song.>

