Scene 1 - 1 : A Meeting of the Bored

<LIGHTS: The scene opens in the boardroom of Fassablanca, Inc. There should be a sign with this name on it clearly visible. 
Les Dewitt and Alec Trolysis are on stage looking nervous.>

Dewitt: Where's the reset of the development team, Alec? I thought they were supposed to report on all the new gadgets they've been coming up with.

Alec: They'll be here any second now, sir. Dr. Tube is busy working on the new company symbol.

<SOUND: The sound of a cymbal>

Alec: There it is now.

Dewitt: Well, then where's Doctor Sacharride. ## As previously noted, spelling varies. ##

Alec: She's busy testing out the new combination shower and gamma-ray chamber.

Dewitt: A combination shower and gamma-ray chamber?

Alec: Uh-huh. You see, gamma rays have the power to turn anyone into a super soldier.

Dewitt: What does that mean?

Alec: Gamma rays rot your brain and turn your skin khaki.

Dewitt: Here's Dr. Saccharride now.

<Polly Sacharride enters, wearing a bathrobe or perhaps only a towel. She is accompanied by Tess Tube.>

Dewitt: It's about time you showed up. Did you try out that new gamma-ray chamber?

Polly: Well, I was going to but I kept putting it off.

Tess: You might say it was a shower stall.

Polly: ... and by the time I finally got in, Seymour was already there.

Dewitt: Seymour?

Polly: I sure did!

Tess: Seymour is the fourth member of our development team. He should be here any minute.

Alec: In the meantime, we can show you some of the great new gadgets we've been coming up with. This, for example,
is our new atomic hand grenade. It can destroy everything within a radius of 30 yards.

Dewitt: That's great!

Tess: Unfortunately, the average person can only throw it 15 feet.

<At this point, Seymour walks in. He is dressed only in purple pants, a la Hulk. He is glowing a bright green.>

Seymour: Hi, everybody.

Polly: Hi, Seymour.

Seymour: Hi, Polly.

Dewitt: He ... he's green!

Tess: Yes, it's a small side effect of the gamma ray chamber.

Dewitt: That's awful!

Tess: Oh it's not that bad. Think of all the advantages being green.

Dewitt: Like what?

Polly: You can get a job in movies as a stand-in for Lorne Green.

Tess: No-one would know when ## sic ## if you accidentally sat on a caterpillar.

Seymour: Hey, watch it! It's not easy being green, y'know.

Dewitt: Well, the gamma ray chamber is no good to us if it has that kind of side effect. What else have you people come up with?

Tess: Well, we do have a new Tommy gun...

Dewitt: It only shoots blind pin-ball players, right?

Tess: Hey, has there been a security leak?

Dewitt: You people haven't come up with a single invention that works! What are you going to tell the big boss when he gets here?

Tess: We could give Seymour a perm and tell everyone he's a broccoli.

<Enter Phil T. Rich, a doddering old fool. He is accompanies by his (ahem) bride, Anna Stesia.>

Anna: Hi, everybody! Sorry the boss and I are late, but our car broke down on the way over.

Phil: Never mind that now; what are all these people doing here?

Dewitt: They work here.

Phil: Oh. And what are you doing here?

Dewitt: I work here too. Don't you remember, I'm Les Dewitt. This is Dr. Tess Tube, Dr. Polly Saccharide, Alec Trolysis, and Seymour...

<Seymour enters greenly>

Dewitt: That's Seymour Clearly.

Phil: Who does he think he is? Kermit the Frog?

Anna; I'd say he's moure like The Incredible Hunk ...

Phil: You say you people work here? Doing what?

Dewitt: They're our R & D team.

Phil: R & D? Relaxation and doodling?

Dewitt: No, Razzle and Dazzle.

Anna: Do any of them know how to fix cars?

Alec: I can fix washing machines!

Seymour: I can fix roulette wheels!

Alec: I can fix card games!

Seymour: I can fix cats!

Dewitt: What part of the car is broken, Anna?

Anna: The back seat.

Dewitt: Why can't you use the front seat?

Anna: There's a stick shift.

Phil: We haven't got time to worry about the car now. If our company doesn't come up with some new gadgets and inventions soon, we'll be out of business. Now what have you got?

Alec: Well, there's the tactile nuclear device.

Anna: Tactile nuclear device?

Alec: I'll show you.

<He exits on the run.>

Tess: Be careful, Alec.

Phil: Did he really mean tactile? I thought the word was _tactical_.

Polly: No, tactile. It only goes off when somebody strokes it.

<SOUND: A small nuclear explosion, offstage left. Alec screams.>

Tess: Aye, there's the rub.

Anna: Poor Alec. Well, at least it was a touching finish.

<Alec enters, somewhat the worse for wear>

Alec: I feel like something I ate last night at the Village.

Tess: Well sir, I'm afraid the tactile nuclear device is a bit of a bomb. But don't you worry, there's lots more where that came from.

Phil: That's what I was afraid of. Haven't you got anything less... dramatic?

Alec: Well, there are the musical robots...

Phil: Musical robots?

Seymour: Uh-huh. We call them the Alcan Can-Can Tin-cans.

Polly: They're sort of electronic singing and dancing automatons.

Phil: Dancing? Can the Alcan Can-Can Tin-cans Can-can?

Polly: Can the Alcan Can-Can Tin-cans Can-can! The Alcan Can-Can Tin-cans can Can-can the cans of every can-canner in Canada.

Phil: Then the Alcan Can-Can Tin-cans are really All-Can Can-Can Tin-cans.

Anna: Can we can this can-can crap?

All: Sure can!

Tess: The robots also tell jokes. Sort of.

Phil: Sort of? What do you mean, sort of?

Alec: We can show you, sir. Bring out the Musical Robots!

<SOUND: Enter the Musical Robots ## Bjorn Cyborg, Nancy Standard Fortran, Fred Buffers, Datanet Funicello, and Otto Mation ## to the tune of the Can-Can, of course.>

Bjorn: What's green, has four legs, and will kill you if it falls out of a tree?

Nancy: I don't know, what?

Bjorn: A pool table.

Buffers: Why do engineers make such good astronauts?

Datanet: No, what happened? ## That's what the script says. Surely, it should be "I don't know. WHY do engineers make such good astronauts?" ##

Fred: Because they took up space in school.

Datanet: What about the girl whose padded bra caught fire?

Otto: It was a falsie alarm.

Nancy: Whatever happened to that Volkswagen you had?

Otto: It broke down.

Nancy: Well, what did you do with it?

Otto: I took it to the Old Volks Home.

Buffers: Is it true you're going out with a butcher?

Datanet: Yup, I'm playing for big steaks.

Phil: <To Tess> I think I know what you mean by sort of.

Alec: Well, they have lots of other talents, too. For example, they sing.

Phil: Do they have to?

Seymour: Uh-huh. Just watch!

