Phil: Enough of this! Where on earth do you people come up with these things, anyway? Musical robots! More like musical trash cans! Get out of here.

<The robots exit.>

Phil: NOw would somebody like to tell me where we're going to come up with all the new inventions this company needs? Hmm?

Alec: Well sir, I've been meaning to address that very question. If you could just give us a bit more time...

Polly: Yes, we should have something soon... just a few more days...

Phil: You don't have a few more days. I want some action and I want it now.

Anna: Now? Right here? In front of the scientists?

Phil: Not that kind of action.

Dewitt: Maybe we could just steal some ideas from someone else!

Polly: That's silly!

Alec: It's ridiculous!

Tess: It's absurd.

Seymour: It's just dumb.

Phil: I like it.

Others: Me too.

Phil: Now where are you going to steal the ideas from?

Dewitt: Well, maybe I have an idea. You know how governments spend billions of dollars coming up with all sorts of new gadgets and stuff?

Polly: But everyone else finds out about things like that the same time we do.

Dewitt: That's right, but half the stuff they come up with, no one ever finds out about because it's top secret. Maybe we could hire a bunch of spies to steal those secrets so we can come out with a line of products that will make us the envy of our competitions and make us rich beyond our wildest dreams!!!

Tess: Hey, that's a good idea! And while they are at it, they might as well pick up any secret war plans they happen to run across, too.

Phil: I like it! No government would ever believe anything but another government would dar eto steal its secrets.

Alec: But sir, where on earth are we going to find a bunch of spies. We'd have better luck getting a bushel of MacIntoshes.

Phil: Shut up, you fruit. Any ideas, gentlemen?

Dewitt: We could get N.A.S.T.Y. !

Polly, Alec, Tess, Seymour: Nasty?

Polly: With whom?

Dewitt: No, the National Albanian Spy Team Youth. I saw an add for them in the Chevron. Better yet, we could hire C.U.S.O. to do it.

Phil: CUSO?

Dewitt: The Canadian Union of Spies Overseas.

Anna: I didn't know there were any Canadian spies overseas. I thought the only undercover agents we had were the Mounties.

Dewitt: You can forget about them. They tried to handle a mission overseas once, and their horses drowned.

Phil: Look, why don't we just take out an ad in the paper and be done with it?

Dewitt: Right away, sir. But what paper? The Gazette? The Imprint? Enginews?

Phil: <Beginning to exit> Who reads those rags? Go for te best: the Waterloo Chronicle.

<Phil and Anna exit.>

Tess: This is awful! If they get a bunch of spies to steal inventions, they don't need us anymore.

Alec: Don't worry, kid. Always look on the bright side of life.

